The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA Gallery, 11 am-8 pm, till September 28) The exhibition-cum-sale 

 showcases artefacts in dokra, tribal art, decorative 

 arts, wall hangings, jewellery, textiles, stoles and scarves, 

 linen, mats, carpets, dhurries, ready-to-wear, bags and 

 books. 

 THE FILM FEST

 (Seagull Bookstore, 6 pm, till September 25)The Seagull 

 Foundation for the Arts presents the festival of films on 

 America. Roger amp; Me is on September 18; Wal 

 Mart: The High Cost of Low Price will be shown the following 

 day. The Corporation is slated for September 20 and 

 The Road to Guantanamo on September 21. Enron: 

 The Smartest Guys in the Room will be screened on September 

 22 and Hearts amp; Minds on September 25. 

 THE BOOK

 (Oxford 

 Bookstore, 6.30 pm, September 18) The Penguin publication, 

 Selected Stories by Parashuram, translated from Bengali 

 by Sukanta Chaudhuri and Palash Baran Pal, will be launched 

 with dramatised readings from the book. the play 

 (UMA 

 Gallery, 6 pm and 8 pm, September 20-24) Tin Can presents 

 Intro, an hour-long play in English and Bengali designed 

 by Soumyak Kanti De Biswas. Tickets available at the British 

 Council. 




